Q. Why hasn't the Skyscraper Engineer responded
to the wishes of the majority of the engineering
student by including the Techni-Cutie?
A. A majority of engineering students didn't vote
to place the Techni-Cutie feature in the Skyscraper.
570 names were on the petitions and that isn't a
majority of undergraduate engineers. The feature
didn't agree with our policy of depicting all minority
and socially sensitive groups as whole individuals
rather than archaic stereotypes. As with the Pitt
News and other University student publications,
Editorial policy is determined by the student editor.
