the University Faculty or directly by the student
body.


Q. Has the word spread that Pitt Engineering
School is improving?
A. One of the most lasting and hardest things to
change is the reputation of a school. I know of one
Chemical Engineering department at a school I
won't mention which was tops when I was in school
but today I wouldn't recommend it for a graduate
school for one of our graduates. It, however, still has
a widely held reputation of being one of the best.
Pitt Engineering School is respected coast to coast
and we are always trying to spread the word of our
improvements. We've come a long way in a short
time.

