    In general, the important points to note in this area are:
    1. The ultrafiltration flux is inversely proportional to the protein
concentration.
    2. The flux is approximately proportional to the rate of mixing.
    3. The flux pressure curves are extremely non linear when
ultrafiltering protein solutions. (not shown).
    The decay in ultrafiltration flux occurs as the result of proteins
accumulating on the surface. This accumulation is due to the fact that
protein arrival by convection is greater than their rate of diffusion
away.
